<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="106" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/5–641</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                                (<hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-06">May 6, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>We have clear indication that Admiral [Nomura] is having to try to “sell”
                            to his Government (at least his Foreign Office) the project for an
                            agreement between Japan and the United States, to which project the John
                            Doe associates have been telling us that the Japanese controlling
                            authorities (the backers of Colonel [Itakuro]) are already committed in
                            principle.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>